        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 12 at 3:59PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 359 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 10
miles north of Columbus, or 4 miles south of Bat Cave, moving
northeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Lake Lure, Chimney Rock Village, Chimney Rock State Park, and Bat
Cave.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
